{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Why\nThe delivered epic (Gerrit stack 558/560/561/563/576/579/580/581, NOT landed) diverged\nfrom the APPROVED epic design on the authorship-payload format. bde5 (change 561) signs\nthe event's RAW canonical bytes; the approved AC requires an **in-toto Statement**\npayload. This story transitions the delivered code to the approved design. (User rejected\nthe delivered design; full divergence record in session_log d7c0.)\n\n## What\nRework `attest/authorship.py` so authorship signatures wrap an **in-toto Statement**:\n\n- **Statement schema (exact).** The signed payload is an in-toto Statement JSON object:\n  - `_type`: `\"https://in-toto.io/Statement/v1\"`\n  - `subject`: a one-element array `[{ \"name\": \"<event_uuid>\", \"digest\": { \"sha256\": \"<content_hash>\" } }]`\n    where `name` carries the event_uuid and `digest.sha256` carries the content_hash.\n  - `predicateType`: `\"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\"`\n  - `predicate`: `{}` (empty; authorship asserts binding only, no extra claims).\n  - `content_hash` = **SHA-256, lowercase hex**, over the event's canonical JSON bytes\n    with the `author_sig` key EXCLUDED (so the signature never covers itself).\n- **DSSE envelope.** The Statement JSON (UTF-8, canonical) is the DSSE `payload`;\n  `payloadType = application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json`; signed over\n  `PAE(payloadType, payload)` via the foundation SSHSIG scheme (substrate unchanged).\n- `sign_authorship(event, key_path, identity_id)` computes content_hash, builds the\n  Statement, wraps it in a DSSE envelope, returns the encoded envelope.\n- `verify_authorship(event, envelope, trust_root)` (1) parses the DSSE payload as an\n  in-toto Statement, (2) checks `subject[0].name == event_uuid` AND\n  `subject[0].digest.sha256 == recomputed content_hash(event minus author_sig)`, (3)\n  THEN verifies the DSSE signature against the identity's in-band keys. Any parse/shape\n  failure or mismatch yields a non-verified result; verify NEVER raises on lookup error.\n- The write seam (`_seam.py`) stamps `author_sig` = the DSSE-encoded Statement envelope,\n  hashing the canonical event minus author_sig.\n- Add the epic-AC-named `create_placeholder(provider, external_id, display_name)` path.\n\n## Consumer that MUST change in THIS story (content-binding)\n`src/rebar/_commands/verify_authorship.py` currently re-derives the raw canonical event\nbytes and compares `envelope.payload != ev.payload` (its content-binding check). Once the\npayload becomes an in-toto Statement, that raw-bytes compare would classify EVERY signed\nevent as bad-signature. This story updates that content-binding check to parse the\nStatement and compare `subject[0].digest.sha256` to the recomputed content_hash (event\nminus author_sig) — the payload-format contract. (Out of scope here, deferred to TS3/3183:\nthe SNAPSHOT ledger schema and the `key_not_valid_at_era` verdict — this story only aligns\nthe payload/content-binding so the merge-gate keeps working on the reworked payload.)\n\n## create_placeholder rationale\nEpic AC1 explicitly names `create_placeholder(provider, external_id, display_name)`; the\ndelivered code shipped the equivalent `ensure_identity_for` but not the AC-named surface.\nThis adds the named entry as a thin idempotent alias over `ensure_identity_for` to restore\nthe approved public surface (mandated by the epic AC, not surface proliferation).\n\n## Landing / sequencing (why no dual-format window is needed)\nTS1–TS4 land as ONE ATOMIC Gerrit stack submit (relation chain; the top submits its\nancestors) — there is no runtime window where TS1 is live on `main` without TS2/TS3. Each\nintermediate patchset must still be internally green, which is exactly why this story also\nupdates `verify_authorship.py`'s content-binding (above), so the bde5' patchset verifies\nits own reworked payload. Write-time signing is opt-in (`identity.require_authenticated`\ndefault off + a configured signing key) and the stack is unlanded, so NO persisted event\ncarries an old-format `author_sig` — no migration/backfill is required. The docs/ADR\ncapturing this pivot are rewritten in TS4 (b134).\n\n## Scope\nIn: in-toto Statement authorship payload (sign/verify/content_hash), the `author_sig`\nwrite-seam stamping, the `verify_authorship.py` content-binding update to the Statement,\nand the `create_placeholder` alias. Out: era/validity model (TS2/e165), the SNAPSHOT\nledger schema + `key_not_valid_at_era` verdict (TS3/3183), docs/ADR (TS4).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `sign_authorship` produces a DSSE envelope whose payload is an in-toto Statement\n  (`_type` https://in-toto.io/Statement/v1, `predicateType`\n  application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json) with `subject[0] = {name: event_uuid,\n  digest: {sha256: content_hash}}`; a test asserts the structure + payloadType.\n- [ ] `content_hash` is SHA-256 hex over the canonical event with `author_sig` EXCLUDED;\n  a test proves adding/removing `author_sig` does not change the content_hash, and that\n  mutating any other field DOES change it.\n- [ ] `verify_authorship` verifies an event signed by identity A against A's in-band\n  keys; a test asserts it does NOT verify against identity B, FAILS on a tampered event\n  (payload/content_hash mismatch), and FAILS on a tampered signature.\n- [ ] `verify_authorship.py`'s content-binding check reads the in-toto Statement's\n  `subject[0].digest.sha256` (not raw-bytes compare); an end-to-end test signs an event\n  through the write seam and asserts `verify-authorship` classifies it `verified`, proving\n  the raw-bytes compare path is gone.\n- [ ] An unavailable signing key yields an `unsigned` (Tier-0) write, never a blocked\n  write (test).\n- [ ] `create_placeholder(provider, external_id, display_name)` mints a keyless\n  placeholder identity, idempotent on repeat (test).\n\n## file_impact\n- `src/rebar/attest/authorship.py` (in-toto Statement build/parse + content_hash)\n- `src/rebar/_commands/_seam.py` (stamp author_sig = DSSE Statement envelope)\n- `src/rebar/_commands/verify_authorship.py` (content-binding reads Statement subject digest)\n- `src/rebar/_commands/identity.py` (create_placeholder alias over ensure_identity_for)"}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783881514726766001,"uuid":"8b0f17cf-b48e-4a5b-a8df-0caa69d3a96b"}